# Thesis Dashboard — Information Architecture

## Structure

Four primary routes, one thesis per page:

| Route         | Page            | Thesis question                                                   |
|---------------|-----------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `/`           | HomePage        | What is the research about? (Two claim cards)                     |
| `/mechanism`  | MechanismPage   | How does one round work, and why is the mechanism well-defined?   |
| `/results`    | ResultsPage (Comparisons) | Fixed benchmark comparisons; what changes when skill enters the weighting? |
| `/robustness` | RobustnessPage  | Does it hold up under missingness, sybil, and parameter changes?  |

Legacy interactive tools live at `/appendix` (LabPage) and `/appendix/experiments`.

## Claims

**Claim 1** — The mechanism is coherent: deposits, effective wagers, aggregation, refunds, and payouts are jointly defined and satisfy core accounting checks.

**Claim 2** — Online skill weighting reduces the damage from noisy stake and improves over stake-only weighting, but equal weighting remains a strong benchmark. Present results honestly.

## Semantic tokens (`lib/tokens.ts`)

Use the `SEM` colour map everywhere for consistency:

- deposit (b) — sky blue `#0ea5e9`
- skill (σ) — violet `#8b5cf6`
- effective wager (m) — indigo `#6366f1`
- aggregate (r̂) — teal `#0d9488`
- score (s) — amber `#f59e0b`
- payoff (Π) — emerald `#10b981`
- outcome (y) — red `#ef4444`
- wealth (W) — pink `#ec4899`

## Terminology (use one term per object)

- **deposit** (b) — not "stake" or "wager"
- **skill** (σ) — not "weight" or "ability"
- **effective wager** (m) — not "influence"
- **score** (s) — not "accuracy"
- **payoff** (Π) — total payout
- **profit** (π) — payoff minus deposit

## Copy rules

- Every page: one question, one answer, one takeaway
- No intro paragraph longer than 2 sentences
- Every chart: title, what is being compared, one-line conclusion
- Notation defined once in `GLOSSARY_ENTRIES` and reused via `StickyGlossary`

## Key files

- `src/lib/tokens.ts` — semantic colours, method colours, glossary
- `src/components/dashboard/StickyGlossary.tsx` — floating glossary button
- `src/components/lab/shared.ts` — chart constants, formatters, agent palette
- `src/lib/coreMechanism/runPipeline.ts` — core simulation engine
- `src/lib/store.tsx` — app state (experiment, round, DGP, behaviour)

## Core equations

```
m_{i,t} = b_{i,t}(λ + (1−λ)σ_{i,t})
Π^{skill}_{i,t} = m_{i,t}(1 + s_{i,t} − s̄_t)
```

## Do not

- Add thesis prose or literature review text to the UI
- Alternate between "stake", "wager", "deposit" without explicit distinction
- Overclaim that skill weighting always beats baselines
- Add routes to the primary sidebar beyond the four listed above
